CSS transitions provide a way to control animation speed when changing CSS properties. Instead having property changes take effect immediately, to control animation speed when changing CSS properties. Instead having property changes take effect immediately, you can also cause the change to take place over a period of time or instantaneously.
     With CSS transitions enabled, changing occur at time intervals that follow an acceleration curve, all of which can be customized.
	HTML
<Body>
<P> The box below combine transitions for: width, height, background-color, transform on hover the box to see these properties animated.

	CSS
.box{
	Border-style: solid;
	Border-width: 1px;
	Display: block;
	Width: 100px;
	Height: 100px;
	Background-color: #0000FF;
	Webkit-transition: width 2s, height 2s background-color 2s, webkit-transform 2s.
	Transition: width 2s, height 2s background-color 2s, transform 2s.
     }
.box: hover {
Background-color: #FFCCC;
Width: 200
Height:
Webkit-transform: rotate (180deg) 
Transform: rotate (180deg)

                                                           WEB DESIGN & DEVELOPMENT
                                                                          
                                                                          
                                                                          
CSS properties used to define transitions sited: https://developer.mozilla.org
CSS Transitions are controlled using the short hand Transition Property. This is the best way to configure transitions, as it makes it easier to avoid that, the length of the parameter list are out of Sync.
Which can be very frustrating to have to spend lot of time debugging the CSS.

    Transition-property
   
	Specifies the names or name of the CSS properties to which transitions should be applied. Only properties listed here are animated during transitions;
All other properties occur instantaneous as usaual.


      Transition-duration

	Specifies the duration over which transitions should occur. You can specify a single duration that applies to all properties during the transition, or multiple value to allow each property transition over different period of time.


Transition-delay

	Define how long to wait between the time a property is changed and the transition actually begins.



	
