•	Continue to grow while rending additional contact


                          MD Material.io Bottom-navigation
                          
Bottom navigation bars make it easy to explore and switch top-level views in a single-tap.
Bottom navigation is primary for use on mobile to achieve a  similar effect for desktop use side navigations.


	
                      Alternative Tabs {Scrollable Tabs}
Tabs makes it easy to explore and switch between different views.

Tabs create/enable content organization at a high level  such as switching between views data sets of  functional aspect of an app.




                                                           Web Development & Design
                                                                      
                                                                      
                                                                      
          Materials Design
                    Using {Scrollable Tabs}
                    
Scrollable tabs display a subset moment. They can contain larger to number of tabs than fixed tabs,

Best Using For Browsing Contexts

                            How to navigate
                            
To navigate between scrollable tabs, the content area left or right.
To scroll tabs without navigating, swipe the tabs left or right.







              Fixed Tabs Display
              
              
              
The width of each tab can be calculated by taking the width of the new an dividing it by the number of tabs. Alternatively, make all tabs the width the largest tabs.

If margin between the tabs edge and view edge is 16dp or LESS, use full width tabs instead of center tabs.

By using standard platform implementations you will review related future improvement.



                                                       CSS 3: Using Pseudo-classes
                                                                          
                                                                          
Pseudo-element and pseudo-classes can be used without assigning those element in the HTML.
              
                Targeting Specific Element with or without using 10s or classes
                
                
Like attribute selectors, pseudo-classes and pseudo-elements can be used to select specific element in the HTML.
With or without assigning those elements 10s or classes, keeping your markup cleaner.
Pseudo-classes and pseudo-elements target pieces of HTML that either don’t exist as standalone element or do exist, but have unique characteristic that you can’t target with the other simple selectors.

          
Pseudo-classes	Description
:root                                                             Selects the element that is the root of the document. In HTML, this is 
                                                                      always the HTML element.








:nth-child ()                                                  Select based on the position within the list of its parent’s children.







:nth-last-child ()                                           Same as :nth-child (), but the counting for the position number is done
                                                                       From the last child upward instead of the first child downward.







:nth-of-type ()                                                Select based on position within the list of its parent children, but only                                                                     
                                                                          counting children of certain type.                                                                                  





:nth-last-of-type ()                                            Same as nth-of-type (), but counting from the last child of the specified 
                                                                            Type instead of the first.






                                       





                                                          Web Design & Development
                                                                                   
                                                                                   

                      HTML & CSS
                            Class Selectors
                            
In CSS we use selectors to interact with our HTML, there are many different types of CSS selectors that allows you to target rules to specific elements in an HTML document.



Class                                           matches an element whose class attribute has a value                         .note { }
                                                     that matches the one Specified after the pen.                                          P.note { }


10 selector                                  matches an element whose id attribute has a value that                         #introduction { }
                                                      matches the one Specified after the pound or hash symbols.


Child selector                              matches an element that is a direct child of another.                                 Li> a { }


Descendant selector                    matches an elements that is a descendant of another                              p a { }
                                                        Specified element (not just a direct child of that element).




Universal selector                           applies to all element in the pages.                                                          * { }




                                                        Web Design & Development
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
            HTML & CSS
                    How CSS Rules cascade
                    
                   

If there are two or more rules that apply to the same element, it is important to understand which will take precedence.

        Last Rule
        
If one selector is more specific than the others, the more specific rule will take precedence over more general ones.
P #intro p b                                          *p h1

Most specific                                least specific


          Important 
          
You can add important after any property value to indicate that it should be considered more important than other rules that apply to the same element.
